/span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2534121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 17, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104yjg1665702916894.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yjg1665702916894.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/yjg1665702916894.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"yjg1665702916894\" role=\"article\">\n<div class=\"body refbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Close a table. </p>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__section_cpj_53q_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1008762e50\">Description</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__p_d129992e1_d129993e1_d129994e1\">Close the table corresponding to the current\n          <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl</code> structure and free all resources used for that table. Update the\n        number of open files and open cursors. If the DBMS does not support table closing, return 0\n        to Uniface.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__p_d129995e1_d129996e1_d129997e1\">If a file pointer or file handle was stored in the\n        connector workspace in the Open call, it can be used to close the table.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__section_ccs_1bx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1008762e64\">From Uniface</h2>Preconditions realized by\n      Uniface—when the <code class=\"ph codeph\">Close</code> request is called, the connector is logged on to the\n      DBMS and the table corresponding to the current <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl</code> structure is\n        open.<div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 1. </span><span class=\"title\">Information Available from Uniface</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__1\">Data Structure-&gt;Element </th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__2\">Description </th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;TMEnabled</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__2\">Indicates whether the connector is\n                TM-controlled.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrv</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__2\">Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was\n                requested in the Info call. </td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrvini</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__2\">Identification of the current logon path.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__1\"><code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;uname</code></td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15476e1_d15477e1_d15478e1__entry__2\">Points to the table name.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div></section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__section_whb_fbx_bcc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1008762e142\">To Uniface</h2><div class=\"table-wrap\"><table class=\"table\" count-columns=\"2\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1\"><caption><span class=\"table--title-label\">Table 2. </span><span class=\"title\">Connector Return Values</span></caption><colgroup><col/><col/></colgroup><thead class=\"thead\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__1\">Value</th>\n<th class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__2\">Description</th>\n</tr>\n</thead><tbody class=\"tbody\">\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__1\">0</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__2\">Close was successful. The specified table is\n                closed.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__1\">-3</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__2\">Exceptional error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__1\">-9 </td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__2\">I/O server logon error.</td>\n</tr>\n<tr class=\"row\" dir=\"ltr\">\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__1\">-16</td>\n<td class=\"entry\" dir=\"ltr\" headers=\"yjg1665702916894__table_d15479e1_d15480e1_d15481e1__entry__2\">DBMS reported network error.</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody></table></div>When the connector request return value is less than 0, an error code must be supplied\n      in <code class=\"ph codeph\">uctrl-&gt;udrverr</code>.</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__section_k2b_ngw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1008762e214\">Service Functions</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Refer the following service functions that are related to <code class=\"ph codeph\">Close ('Z')</code>:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__ul_wlc_qgw_fwb\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__li_d46709e1_d46710e1_d46711e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"prf1665702918304.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/prf1665702918304.html\" title=\"Return the number of open operating system files.\">udfilcnt</a> — Update the number\n          of open files. </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__li_d46712e1_d46713e1_d46714e1\"><a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"fjd1665702918235.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/fjd1665702918235.html\" title=\"Return the number of open database cursors.\">udcurscnt</a> — Update the number\n          of open cursors. </li>\n</ul>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__section_ug4_3gw_fwb\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d1008762e247\">TM-Controlled Connectors</h2>\n<p class=\"p\">Connectors that are TM-controlled do not receive Commit and Rollback requests. Therefore,\n        connectors that normally perform cursor administration at the end of a transaction may not\n        be able to determine whether a particular cursor is open or closed when the connector is\n        TM-controlled.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__p_d130019e1_d130020e1_d130021e1\">TM-controlled connectors that use the Close request to\n        close cursors may not be able to distinguish between open cursors and those that were closed\n        implicitly by the DBMS at the end of a transaction. These connectors can choose to ignore an\n        error from the DBMS which indicates that a cursor was already closed.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"yjg1665702916894__p_d130022e1_d130023e1_d130024e1\">TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin,\n        commit or rollback transactions.</p>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/azl1665702915888.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>uctrl</a><p>Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/xrb1665702976299.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors</a><p>A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2534121\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Close ('Z') Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 17, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Close a table. Description Close the table corresponding to the current uctrl structure and free all resources used for that table. Update the number of open files and open cursors. If the DBMS does not support table closing, return 0 to Uniface. If a file pointer or file handle was stored in the connector workspace in the Open call, it can be used to close the table. From Uniface Preconditions realized by Uniface—when the Close request is called, the connector is logged on to the DBMS and the table corresponding to the current uctrl structure is open. Table 1. Information Available from Uniface Data Structure->Element Description uctrl->TMEnabled Indicates whether the connector is TM-controlled. uctrl->udrv Points to the connector workspace if a workspace was requested in the Info call. uctrl->udrvini Identification of the current logon path. uctrl->uname Points to the table name. To Uniface Table 2. Connector Return Values Value Description 0 Close was successful. The specified table is closed. -3 Exceptional error. -9 I/O server logon error. -16 DBMS reported network error. When the connector request return value is less than 0, an error code must be supplied in uctrl->udrverr . Service Functions Refer the following service functions that are related to Close ('Z') : udfilcnt — Update the number of open files. udcurscnt — Update the number of open cursors. TM-Controlled Connectors Connectors that are TM-controlled do not receive Commit and Rollback requests. Therefore, connectors that normally perform cursor administration at the end of a transaction may not be able to determine whether a particular cursor is open or closed when the connector is TM-controlled. TM-controlled connectors that use the Close request to close cursors may not be able to distinguish between open cursors and those that were closed implicitly by the DBMS at the end of a transaction. These connectors can choose to ignore an error from the DBMS which indicates that a cursor was already closed. TM-controlled connectors are not allowed to begin, commit or rollback transactions. Related Links uctrl Exchanges general information between Uniface and the connector, and describes a table. TM-Controlled DBMS Connectors A database connector can be controlled by a transaction manager only if it is TM-capable. Uniface does not provide TM-controlled connectors and does not directly support third-party transaction managers. However, you can use the APIs provided by the Database Connector Interface to build a custom database connector that does. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}